[2026-03-18T17:36:20.785Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EEhfGToBDHTMQs7ykfBKLf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ErSSv2TbXZXABPHgVR3xit","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/networkProxy.ts"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":348,"cache_read_input_tokens":14225,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":348,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AusAuTVWFD2XBKVmR4gsG4","session_id":"4ac23663-2b94-4a88-95a8-b1d1a8af070a","uuid":"cf14192c-f23e-4a88-92dc-ca014de6b47a"}
[2026-03-18T17:36:20.881Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ErSSv2TbXZXABPHgVR3xit","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n     2→// Filtering HTTP CONNECT proxy for per-persona network policies\n     3→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n     4→\n     5→import http from 'node:http';\n     6→import net from 'node:net';\n     7→import type { Duplex } from 'node:stream';\n     8→import type { Logger } from 'pino';\n     9→import { type NetworkPolicyRule, isAllowed, type NetworkPolicy } from '@dac-cloud/shared';\n    10→\n    11→export interface ProxyHandle {\n    12→  port: number;\n    13→  cleanup: () => void;\n    14→}\n    15→\n    16→export async function startFilterProxy(\n    17→  policy: NetworkPolicy,\n    18→  logger: Logger,\n    19→  executionId: string,\n    20→): Promise<ProxyHandle> {\n    21→  const activeSockets = new Set<net.Socket | Duplex>();\n    22→  let allowedCount = 0;\n    23→  let blockedCount = 0;\n    24→\n    25→  const server = http.createServer((_req, res) => {\n    26→    // Non-CONNECT requests through proxy — check and forward or reject\n    27→    const url = _req.url;\n    28→    if (!url) { res.writeHead(400).end(); return; }\n    29→    try {\n    30→      const parsed = new URL(url);\n    31→      const port = parseInt(parsed.port, 10) || (parsed.protocol === 'https:' ? 443 : 80);\n    32→      if (!isAllowed(policy, parsed.hostname, port)) {\n    33→        blockedCount++;\n    34→        logger.warn({ executionId, host: parsed.hostname, port }, 'Proxy: blocked non-CONNECT request');\n    35→        res.writeHead(403, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' }).end('Blocked by network policy');\n    36→        return;\n    37→      }\n    38→      allowedCount++;\n    39→    } catch (err) {\n    40→      logger.warn({ err, executionId, operation: 'proxy_parse_url' }, 'Proxy URL parse error');\n    41→      res.writeHead(400).end();\n    42→      return;\n    43→    }\n    44→    // For allowed non-CONNECT, pass through (minimal — most traffic uses CONNECT)\n    45→    res.writeHead(501).end('Direct proxy not supported, use CONNECT');\n    46→  });\n    47→\n    48→  server.on('connect', (req, clientSocket, head) => {\n    49→    const target = req.url ?? '';\n    50→    let host: string;\n    51→    let port: number;\n    52→\n    53→    // Parse CONNECT target, handling both IPv4 \"host:port\" and IPv6 \"[::1]:port\"\n    54→    if (target.startsWith('[')) {\n    55→      const closeBracket = target.indexOf(']');\n    56→      host = closeBracket > 0 ? target.slice(1, closeBracket) : '';\n    57→      const portStr = closeBracket > 0 ? target.slice(closeBracket + 2) : '';\n    58→      port = parseInt(portStr, 10) || 443;\n    59→    } else {\n    60→      const lastColon = target.lastIndexOf(':');\n    61→      host = lastColon > 0 ? target.slice(0, lastColon) : target;\n    62→      port = lastColon > 0 ? parseInt(target.slice(lastColon + 1), 10) || 443 : 443;\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    if (!host || !isAllowed(policy, host, port)) {\n    66→      blockedCount++;\n    67→      logger.warn({ executionId, host, port }, 'Proxy: blocked CONNECT');\n    68→      clientSocket.write('HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n    69→      clientSocket.destroy();\n    70→      return;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    allowedCount++;\n    74→\n    75→    const serverSocket = net.connect(port, host, () => {\n    76→      clientSocket.write('HTTP/1.1 200 Connection Established\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n    77→      serverSocket.write(head);\n    78→      serverSocket.pipe(clientSocket);\n    79→      clientSocket.pipe(serverSocket);\n    80→    });\n    81→\n    82→    activeSockets.add(clientSocket);\n    83→    activeSockets.add(serverSocket);\n    84→\n    85→    const removeSocket = (s: net.Socket | Duplex) => { activeSockets.delete(s); };\n    86→\n    87→    serverSocket.on('close', () => removeSocket(serverSocket));\n    88→    clientSocket.on('close', () => removeSocket(clientSocket));\n    89→\n    90→    serverSocket.on('error', (err) => {\n    91→      logger.error({ err, executionId, host, port }, 'Proxy: upstream connection error');\n    92→      clientSocket.destroy();\n    93→    });\n    94→\n    95→    clientSocket.on('error', (err) => {\n    96→      logger.warn({ err, executionId, host, port, operation: 'proxy_client_socket' }, 'Proxy: client socket error');\n    97→      serverSocket.destroy();\n    98→    });\n    99→  });\n   100→\n   101→  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n   102→    server.listen(0, '127.0.0.1', () => {\n   103→      const addr = server.address() as net.AddressInfo;\n   104→      logger.info({ executionId, port: addr.port, mode: policy.mode, rules: policy.allowedHosts?.length ?? 0 }, 'Network filter proxy started');\n   105→      resolve({\n   106→        port: addr.port,\n   107→        cleanup: () => {\n   108→          logger.info({ executionId, allowedCount, blockedCount }, 'Network filter proxy stopping');\n   109→          for (const socket of activeSockets) {\n   110→            socket.destroy();\n   111→          }\n   112→          activeSockets.clear();\n   113→          server.close();\n   114→        },\n   115→      });\n   116→    });\n   117→  });\n   118→}\n   119→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AusAuTVWFD2XBKVmR4gsG4","session_id":"4ac23663-2b94-4a88-95a8-b1d1a8af070a","uuid":"706c16e8-65ce-4021-9491-0ad411b9ea23","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:36:20.785Z"}
[2026-03-18T17:36:57.147Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a10de6e82459cc0c1","tool_use_id":"toolu_01AusAuTVWFD2XBKVmR4gsG4","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore worker package structure","usage":{"total_tokens":34264,"tool_uses":9,"duration_ms":46466},"uuid":"8c0b0482-0441-4040-9980-fe455e2c978b","session_id":"4ac23663-2b94-4a88-95a8-b1d1a8af070a"}
[2026-03-18T17:36:57.147Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AusAuTVWFD2XBKVmR4gsG4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read all the key files. Let me compile a comprehensive report for you.\n\n## Worker Package Structure\n\n**File Listing** (all TypeScript files in `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/`):\n- config.ts\n- connection.ts\n- executor.ts\n- index.ts\n- sandbox.ts\n- parser.ts\n- credentialInjector.ts\n- networkProxy.ts\n\n---\n\n## 1. CONFIG (config.ts)\n\n**Structure**: Loads environment variables into a `WorkerConfig` interface.\n\n```typescript\nexport interface WorkerConfig {\n  orchestratorUrl: string;\n  workerToken: string;\n  workerId: string;\n  imageDigest: string;\n  claudeCliVersion: string;\n  tlsCaPath: string;\n  tlsCertPath: string;\n  tlsKeyPath: string;\n  tlsRejectUnauthorized: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Patterns**:\n- Required vars: `ORCHESTRATOR_URL`, `WORKER_TOKEN`\n- Optional vars: `WORKER_ID` (generates random `worker-{8-char-nanoid}` if missing), `IMAGE_DIGEST`, `CLAUDE_CLI_VERSION`, TLS paths\n- TLS rejection defaults to `true` unless explicitly set to `'false'`\n- No structured config file — purely environment-variable driven\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONNECTION (connection.ts)\n\n**State Management** — The `Connection` class tracks:\n- `ws: WebSocket | null` — active WebSocket connection\n- `connected: boolean` — connection state flag\n- `reconnectDelay` — exponential backoff (1s → 30s max)\n- `heartbeatTimer` / `reconnectTimer` — scheduled timers\n- `shuttingDown: boolean` — graceful shutdown flag\n- `cachedTlsOptions` — pre-read TLS cert/key/ca (cached at init, never re-read)\n- `imageDigest` / `claudeCliVersion` — metadata sent in hello\n\n**Connection Flow**:\n1. `connect()` creates WebSocket with Bearer token auth\n2. On open: sends `hello` message with capabilities (`['claude-cli', 'node', 'git', 'network-policy']`), starts 30s heartbeat\n3. Receives `ack` from orchestrator → calls `sendReady()`\n4. Handles incoming message types: `ack`, `assign`, `cancel`, `shutdown`, `heartbeat`\n5. On close/error: schedules reconnect with exponential backoff (up to 30s)\n\n**Callback Triggers** (from orchestrator):\n- `onAssign(ExecAssign)` — execution assignment\n- `onCancel(ExecCancel)` — cancel execution\n- `onShutdown(OrchestratorShutdown)` — graceful shutdown with grace period\n\n**Send Methods** (worker → orchestrator):\n- `send(msg: WorkerMessage)` — raw send\n- `sendReady()` — worker ready for assignment\n- `sendBusy(executionId, reason)` — already executing\n- `sendStdout/sendStderr(executionId, chunk)` — streaming output\n- `sendComplete(executionId, status, exitCode, durationMs, sessionId?, totalCostUsd?, phaseTimings?)` — execution result\n- `sendProgress(executionId, phase, percent, detail?)` — progress updates\n- `sendEvent(executionId, eventType, payload)` — persona protocol events\n\n---\n\n## 3. EXECUTOR (executor.ts)\n\n**State Tracking**:\n- `childProcess: ChildProcess | null` — currently running CLI process\n- `killed: boolean` — flag tracking if process was killed (vs. exited naturally)\n- `sessionId: string | undefined` — extracted from CLI output\n- `totalCostUsd: number | undefined` — extracted from CLI output\n- `executionDone: Promise<void> | null` — resolves when current execution (including cleanup) finishes\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `isBusy()` → `boolean` — checks if `childProcess !== null`\n- `waitForCleanup(timeoutMs?)` → `Promise<void>` — waits for in-flight execution to complete; returns immediately if idle\n- `execute(assignment, callbacks)` → `Promise<void>` — main execution method\n- `kill()` → terminates process (SIGTERM, then SIGKILL after 5s)\n\n**Execution Flow** (`doExecute`):\n1. **Setup phase** (timing tracked):\n   - `prepareSandbox()` — creates sandbox directory with isolation\n   - `startFilterProxy()` — if network policy requires allow-list\n   - `injectCredentialsViaFile()` — writes credentials to tmpfs file, removes from env\n\n2. **CLI Spawn**:\n   - `spawn(sandbox.command, sandbox.args, { cwd, stdio, env })`\n   - Writes `assignment.prompt` to stdin, ends stdin\n   - Sets timeout (kills process if exceeded)\n\n3. **Output Processing**:\n   - Stdout: line-buffered via `LineBuffer`, each line parsed with `extractStreamEvents()`\n   - Extracts: `sessionId`, `totalCostUsd`, persona protocol events, progress info\n   - Stderr: line-buffered, logged as warnings\n\n4. **Completion**:\n   - Waits for process close event\n   - Flushes remaining buffered output\n   - Always cleanup (finally block):\n     - Deletes credential file\n     - Tears down proxy\n     - Removes sandbox directory\n     - Clears `childProcess`\n   - Calculates `phaseTimings` object with: `sandboxSetupMs`, `proxyStartupMs`, `credentialInjectionMs`, `cliRuntimeMs`, `cleanupMs`\n   - Status: `'cancelled'` (killed), `'completed'` (exit 0), `'failed'` (exit non-0)\n\n---\n\n## 4. INDEX (index.ts) — Entry Point\n\n**Initialization**:\n1. Load config\n2. Install credential exit handler (removes credential files on crash)\n3. Sweep orphaned credential files (cleanup from previous crashes)\n4. Create `Executor` instance\n5. Create `Connection` instance with callbacks\n\n**State**:\n- `currentExecutionId: string | null` — tracks which execution is in-flight\n\n**Callback Wiring**:\n\n**`onAssign`**:\n- If busy (already executing): send `sendBusy()` nack and return\n- Set `currentExecutionId`\n- Call `executor.execute(msg, {...callbacks...})`\n- Callbacks route all stdout/stderr/progress/events to orchestrator via connection\n- On completion: clear `currentExecutionId`, call `sendReady()`\n\n**`onCancel`**:\n- If cancelling current execution: call `executor.kill()`\n\n**`onShutdown`**:\n- If executing: poll `currentExecutionId` every 1s, force kill after grace period\n- Then call graceful `shutdown()`\n\n**Graceful Shutdown** (`shutdown()`):\n- Flag prevents double-shutdown\n- Disconnect from orchestrator\n- **Wait for cleanup**: `executor.waitForCleanup()` ensures sandbox/credential cleanup finishes before `process.exit(0)`\n- This prevents leaking directories or credential files\n\n**Signal Handlers**:\n- SIGINT/SIGTERM: if executing, kill it; then shutdown\n\n---\n\n## 5. SANDBOX (sandbox.ts)\n\n**Configuration Interface**:\n```typescript\nexport interface SandboxConfig {\n  executionId: string;\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  networkAccess: boolean;\n  networkPolicy?: NetworkPolicy;\n  timeoutMs: number;\n  maxBudgetUsd?: number;\n  maxTurns?: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Result Interface**:\n```typescript\nexport interface SandboxResult {\n  command: string;\n  args: string[];\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  cwd: string;\n  sandboxDir: string;\n  proxyRequired?: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n**Two Isolation Modes**:\n\n**1. Full Sandbox (bwrap + namespace isolation)** — when `bubblewrap` is available:\n- Unshare PID, UTS (hostname), network (if no allow-list policy)\n- Read-only mounts: `/usr`, `/bin`, `/sbin`, `/etc/ssl`, `/etc/ca-certificates`, `/usr/local/lib/node_modules`, `/usr/local/bin/claude`\n- Writable per-execution mounts: `/home/exec`, `/workspace`, `/tmp`\n- Network proxy injected via `HTTP_PROXY`, `HTTPS_PROXY`, etc.\n- Command: `bwrap [args] -- claude [cli-args]`\n\n**2. Fallback Sandbox** (no namespace isolation):\n- Requires no network policy (proxy cannot enforce allow-list without namespaces)\n- Sets per-execution `HOME` and `TMPDIR`\n- Direct `claude` command execution\n- Refuses execution if network policy present (would be insecure)\n\n**Environment Cleaning**:\n- `buildCleanEnv()` never inherits `process.env` — only explicit assignment env\n- Sets: `PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin`, `NODE_ENV=production`, `LANG=en_US.UTF-8`\n- Strips `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (handled via file) except non-OAuth keys\n- Removes `CLAUDECODE` (prevents nested Claude Code sessions)\n\n**Credentials**:\n- OAuth tokens (sk-ant-oat*) written to `.claude/.credentials.json` (OAuth JSON)\n- Non-OAuth keys (sk-ant-api*) passed via environment\n- All credentials extracted from assignment env\n\n**Cleanup**:\n- `cleanupSandbox(sandboxDir)` recursively removes sandbox directory with `fs.rmSync(..., { recursive: true, force: true })`\n\n---\n\n## 6. PARSER (parser.ts)\n\n**Extraction Mechanism** — `extractStreamEvents(line)`:\n- Attempts JSON.parse on each stdout line\n- If valid JSON:\n  - Checks for top-level `session_id` or nested in `result.session_id`\n  - Extracts `total_cost_usd` from result messages\n  - Parses assistant messages: searches `message.content[].text` for JSON blocks\n  - Detects persona protocol events: `manual_review`, `user_message`, `persona_action`, `emit_event`\n  - Detects progress: `{ progress: { phase, percent, detail } }`\n\n**LineBuffer**:\n- Buffers incomplete lines\n- `push(chunk)` → returns array of complete lines (trimmed, empty lines skipped)\n- `flush()` → returns any remaining buffered content\n\n---\n\n## 7. CREDENTIAL INJECTOR (credentialInjector.ts)\n\n**State**:\n- `activeCredentialFiles: Set<string>` — tracks all credential files created by this process\n\n**Credential Identification**:\n- Matches keys: `CONNECTOR_*`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `*TOKEN*`, `*SECRET*`, `*PASSWORD*`, `*API_KEY*`\n\n**File Injection**:\n- Writes credentials to tmpfs file (`/dev/shm` on Linux, fallback to `os.tmpdir()`)\n- Filename: `dac-creds-{executionId}-{random8hex}.json`\n- File mode: `0o600` (read-only by owner)\n- Removes credential keys from env (they'll read from file instead)\n- Returns `InjectedCredentials` with path, env key (`DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE`), and cleanup function\n\n**Exit Handler** (`installCredentialExitHandler`):\n- Installed once at startup\n- Runs on process 'exit' event\n- Synchronously removes all tracked credential files\n- Catches failures (logs but doesn't throw)\n\n**Orphan Cleanup** (`sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles`):\n- Scans credential dirs at startup\n- Removes `dac-creds-*` files older than 2 minutes\n- Cleans up files from previous crashes\n\n---\n\n## 8. NETWORK PROXY (networkProxy.ts)\n\n**Proxy Setup** (`startFilterProxy`):\n- HTTP CONNECT proxy (tunneling) for network policy enforcement\n- Listens on `127.0.0.1:0` (random port)\n- Returns `ProxyHandle { port, cleanup }`\n\n**Policy Checking** — uses `isAllowed(policy, host, port)`:\n- Non-CONNECT requests: check URL hostname/port\n- CONNECT requests: parse \"host:port\" (handles IPv6 `[::1]:port`)\n- If blocked: 403 response, destroy socket\n\n**Socket Tracking**:\n- Maintains `Set<net.Socket | Duplex>` of active connections\n- Counters: `allowedCount`, `blockedCount` (logged on cleanup)\n\n**Cleanup**:\n- Destroys all active sockets\n- Closes server\n\n---\n\n## Key Integration Patterns\n\n1. **Execution State Tracking**: `index.ts` maintains `currentExecutionId` to prevent parallel executions. `Executor` tracks `childProcess` and `executionDone` promise for cleanup coordination.\n\n2. **Connection Resilience**: WebSocket reconnect with exponential backoff (1s → 30s). Heartbeat every 30s. Bearer token in headers.\n\n3. **Secure Credential Handling**: Credentials written to tmpfs (not disk or env), removed from env dict, tracked for cleanup, swept on startup for orphans, and deleted in finally block and exit handler.\n\n4. **Cleanup Ordering**: Executor's finally block cleans up credentials, proxy, and sandbox. Main shutdown waits for `waitForCleanup()` before `process.exit()` to prevent leaks.\n\n5. **Isolation Layers**: bwrap namespace isolation (PID, UTS, network) + per-execution sandboxDir + credential file (not env) + network proxy for allow-list policies."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a10de6e82459cc0c1 (use SendMessage with to: 'a10de6e82459cc0c1' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37657\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 46468</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4ac23663-2b94-4a88-95a8-b1d1a8af070a","uuid":"866981e3-2fa3-454e-94cb-32293f42d0a1","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:36:57.036Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the worker package at packages/worker/src/. I need to understand:\n1. The full file listing and structure\n2. How the worker connects (connection.ts)\n3. How executions are tracked (executor.ts)\n4. The worker's entry point (index.ts)\n5. The config (config.ts)\n6. The sandbox setup (sandbox.ts if it exists)\n\nRead all these files completely and report back their full contents and key patterns (how config is structured, how connection state is managed, how execution state is tracked).","agentId":"a10de6e82459cc0c1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've read all the key files. Let me compile a comprehensive report for you.\n\n## Worker Package Structure\n\n**File Listing** (all TypeScript files in `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/worker/src/`):\n- config.ts\n- connection.ts\n- executor.ts\n- index.ts\n- sandbox.ts\n- parser.ts\n- credentialInjector.ts\n- networkProxy.ts\n\n---\n\n## 1. CONFIG (config.ts)\n\n**Structure**: Loads environment variables into a `WorkerConfig` interface.\n\n```typescript\nexport interface WorkerConfig {\n  orchestratorUrl: string;\n  workerToken: string;\n  workerId: string;\n  imageDigest: string;\n  claudeCliVersion: string;\n  tlsCaPath: string;\n  tlsCertPath: string;\n  tlsKeyPath: string;\n  tlsRejectUnauthorized: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Patterns**:\n- Required vars: `ORCHESTRATOR_URL`, `WORKER_TOKEN`\n- Optional vars: `WORKER_ID` (generates random `worker-{8-char-nanoid}` if missing), `IMAGE_DIGEST`, `CLAUDE_CLI_VERSION`, TLS paths\n- TLS rejection defaults to `true` unless explicitly set to `'false'`\n- No structured config file — purely environment-variable driven\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONNECTION (connection.ts)\n\n**State Management** — The `Connection` class tracks:\n- `ws: WebSocket | null` — active WebSocket connection\n- `connected: boolean` — connection state flag\n- `reconnectDelay` — exponential backoff (1s → 30s max)\n- `heartbeatTimer` / `reconnectTimer` — scheduled timers\n- `shuttingDown: boolean` — graceful shutdown flag\n- `cachedTlsOptions` — pre-read TLS cert/key/ca (cached at init, never re-read)\n- `imageDigest` / `claudeCliVersion` — metadata sent in hello\n\n**Connection Flow**:\n1. `connect()` creates WebSocket with Bearer token auth\n2. On open: sends `hello` message with capabilities (`['claude-cli', 'node', 'git', 'network-policy']`), starts 30s heartbeat\n3. Receives `ack` from orchestrator → calls `sendReady()`\n4. Handles incoming message types: `ack`, `assign`, `cancel`, `shutdown`, `heartbeat`\n5. On close/error: schedules reconnect with exponential backoff (up to 30s)\n\n**Callback Triggers** (from orchestrator):\n- `onAssign(ExecAssign)` — execution assignment\n- `onCancel(ExecCancel)` — cancel execution\n- `onShutdown(OrchestratorShutdown)` — graceful shutdown with grace period\n\n**Send Methods** (worker → orchestrator):\n- `send(msg: WorkerMessage)` — raw send\n- `sendReady()` — worker ready for assignment\n- `sendBusy(executionId, reason)` — already executing\n- `sendStdout/sendStderr(executionId, chunk)` — streaming output\n- `sendComplete(executionId, status, exitCode, durationMs, sessionId?, totalCostUsd?, phaseTimings?)` — execution result\n- `sendProgress(executionId, phase, percent, detail?)` — progress updates\n- `sendEvent(executionId, eventType, payload)` — persona protocol events\n\n---\n\n## 3. EXECUTOR (executor.ts)\n\n**State Tracking**:\n- `childProcess: ChildProcess | null` — currently running CLI process\n- `killed: boolean` — flag tracking if process was killed (vs. exited naturally)\n- `sessionId: string | undefined` — extracted from CLI output\n- `totalCostUsd: number | undefined` — extracted from CLI output\n- `executionDone: Promise<void> | null` — resolves when current execution (including cleanup) finishes\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `isBusy()` → `boolean` — checks if `childProcess !== null`\n- `waitForCleanup(timeoutMs?)` → `Promise<void>` — waits for in-flight execution to complete; returns immediately if idle\n- `execute(assignment, callbacks)` → `Promise<void>` — main execution method\n- `kill()` → terminates process (SIGTERM, then SIGKILL after 5s)\n\n**Execution Flow** (`doExecute`):\n1. **Setup phase** (timing tracked):\n   - `prepareSandbox()` — creates sandbox directory with isolation\n   - `startFilterProxy()` — if network policy requires allow-list\n   - `injectCredentialsViaFile()` — writes credentials to tmpfs file, removes from env\n\n2. **CLI Spawn**:\n   - `spawn(sandbox.command, sandbox.args, { cwd, stdio, env })`\n   - Writes `assignment.prompt` to stdin, ends stdin\n   - Sets timeout (kills process if exceeded)\n\n3. **Output Processing**:\n   - Stdout: line-buffered via `LineBuffer`, each line parsed with `extractStreamEvents()`\n   - Extracts: `sessionId`, `totalCostUsd`, persona protocol events, progress info\n   - Stderr: line-buffered, logged as warnings\n\n4. **Completion**:\n   - Waits for process close event\n   - Flushes remaining buffered output\n   - Always cleanup (finally block):\n     - Deletes credential file\n     - Tears down proxy\n     - Removes sandbox directory\n     - Clears `childProcess`\n   - Calculates `phaseTimings` object with: `sandboxSetupMs`, `proxyStartupMs`, `credentialInjectionMs`, `cliRuntimeMs`, `cleanupMs`\n   - Status: `'cancelled'` (killed), `'completed'` (exit 0), `'failed'` (exit non-0)\n\n---\n\n## 4. INDEX (index.ts) — Entry Point\n\n**Initialization**:\n1. Load config\n2. Install credential exit handler (removes credential files on crash)\n3. Sweep orphaned credential files (cleanup from previous crashes)\n4. Create `Executor` instance\n5. Create `Connection` instance with callbacks\n\n**State**:\n- `currentExecutionId: string | null` — tracks which execution is in-flight\n\n**Callback Wiring**:\n\n**`onAssign`**:\n- If busy (already executing): send `sendBusy()` nack and return\n- Set `currentExecutionId`\n- Call `executor.execute(msg, {...callbacks...})`\n- Callbacks route all stdout/stderr/progress/events to orchestrator via connection\n- On completion: clear `currentExecutionId`, call `sendReady()`\n\n**`onCancel`**:\n- If cancelling current execution: call `executor.kill()`\n\n**`onShutdown`**:\n- If executing: poll `currentExecutionId` every 1s, force kill after grace period\n- Then call graceful `shutdown()`\n\n**Graceful Shutdown** (`shutdown()`):\n- Flag prevents double-shutdown\n- Disconnect from orchestrator\n- **Wait for cleanup**: `executor.waitForCleanup()` ensures sandbox/credential cleanup finishes before `process.exit(0)`\n- This prevents leaking directories or credential files\n\n**Signal Handlers**:\n- SIGINT/SIGTERM: if executing, kill it; then shutdown\n\n---\n\n## 5. SANDBOX (sandbox.ts)\n\n**Configuration Interface**:\n```typescript\nexport interface SandboxConfig {\n  executionId: string;\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  networkAccess: boolean;\n  networkPolicy?: NetworkPolicy;\n  timeoutMs: number;\n  maxBudgetUsd?: number;\n  maxTurns?: number;\n}\n```\n\n**Result Interface**:\n```typescript\nexport interface SandboxResult {\n  command: string;\n  args: string[];\n  env: Record<string, string>;\n  cwd: string;\n  sandboxDir: string;\n  proxyRequired?: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n**Two Isolation Modes**:\n\n**1. Full Sandbox (bwrap + namespace isolation)** — when `bubblewrap` is available:\n- Unshare PID, UTS (hostname), network (if no allow-list policy)\n- Read-only mounts: `/usr`, `/bin`, `/sbin`, `/etc/ssl`, `/etc/ca-certificates`, `/usr/local/lib/node_modules`, `/usr/local/bin/claude`\n- Writable per-execution mounts: `/home/exec`, `/workspace`, `/tmp`\n- Network proxy injected via `HTTP_PROXY`, `HTTPS_PROXY`, etc.\n- Command: `bwrap [args] -- claude [cli-args]`\n\n**2. Fallback Sandbox** (no namespace isolation):\n- Requires no network policy (proxy cannot enforce allow-list without namespaces)\n- Sets per-execution `HOME` and `TMPDIR`\n- Direct `claude` command execution\n- Refuses execution if network policy present (would be insecure)\n\n**Environment Cleaning**:\n- `buildCleanEnv()` never inherits `process.env` — only explicit assignment env\n- Sets: `PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin`, `NODE_ENV=production`, `LANG=en_US.UTF-8`\n- Strips `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (handled via file) except non-OAuth keys\n- Removes `CLAUDECODE` (prevents nested Claude Code sessions)\n\n**Credentials**:\n- OAuth tokens (sk-ant-oat*) written to `.claude/.credentials.json` (OAuth JSON)\n- Non-OAuth keys (sk-ant-api*) passed via environment\n- All credentials extracted from assignment env\n\n**Cleanup**:\n- `cleanupSandbox(sandboxDir)` recursively removes sandbox directory with `fs.rmSync(..., { recursive: true, force: true })`\n\n---\n\n## 6. PARSER (parser.ts)\n\n**Extraction Mechanism** — `extractStreamEvents(line)`:\n- Attempts JSON.parse on each stdout line\n- If valid JSON:\n  - Checks for top-level `session_id` or nested in `result.session_id`\n  - Extracts `total_cost_usd` from result messages\n  - Parses assistant messages: searches `message.content[].text` for JSON blocks\n  - Detects persona protocol events: `manual_review`, `user_message`, `persona_action`, `emit_event`\n  - Detects progress: `{ progress: { phase, percent, detail } }`\n\n**LineBuffer**:\n- Buffers incomplete lines\n- `push(chunk)` → returns array of complete lines (trimmed, empty lines skipped)\n- `flush()` → returns any remaining buffered content\n\n---\n\n## 7. CREDENTIAL INJECTOR (credentialInjector.ts)\n\n**State**:\n- `activeCredentialFiles: Set<string>` — tracks all credential files created by this process\n\n**Credential Identification**:\n- Matches keys: `CONNECTOR_*`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `*TOKEN*`, `*SECRET*`, `*PASSWORD*`, `*API_KEY*`\n\n**File Injection**:\n- Writes credentials to tmpfs file (`/dev/shm` on Linux, fallback to `os.tmpdir()`)\n- Filename: `dac-creds-{executionId}-{random8hex}.json`\n- File mode: `0o600` (read-only by owner)\n- Removes credential keys from env (they'll read from file instead)\n- Returns `InjectedCredentials` with path, env key (`DAC_CREDENTIALS_FILE`), and cleanup function\n\n**Exit Handler** (`installCredentialExitHandler`):\n- Installed once at startup\n- Runs on process 'exit' event\n- Synchronously removes all tracked credential files\n- Catches failures (logs but doesn't throw)\n\n**Orphan Cleanup** (`sweepOrphanedCredentialFiles`):\n- Scans credential dirs at startup\n- Removes `dac-creds-*` files older than 2 minutes\n- Cleans up files from previous crashes\n\n---\n\n## 8. NETWORK PROXY (networkProxy.ts)\n\n**Proxy Setup** (`startFilterProxy`):\n- HTTP CONNECT proxy (tunneling) for network policy enforcement\n- Listens on `127.0.0.1:0` (random port)\n- Returns `ProxyHandle { port, cleanup }`\n\n**Policy Checking** — uses `isAllowed(policy, host, port)`:\n- Non-CONNECT requests: check URL hostname/port\n- CONNECT requests: parse \"host:port\" (handles IPv6 `[::1]:port`)\n- If blocked: 403 response, destroy socket\n\n**Socket Tracking**:\n- Maintains `Set<net.Socket | Duplex>` of active connections\n- Counters: `allowedCount`, `blockedCount` (logged on cleanup)\n\n**Cleanup**:\n- Destroys all active sockets\n- Closes server\n\n---\n\n## Key Integration Patterns\n\n1. **Execution State Tracking**: `index.ts` maintains `currentExecutionId` to prevent parallel executions. `Executor` tracks `childProcess` and `executionDone` promise for cleanup coordination.\n\n2. **Connection Resilience**: WebSocket reconnect with exponential backoff (1s → 30s). Heartbeat every 30s. Bearer token in headers.\n\n3. **Secure Credential Handling**: Credentials written to tmpfs (not disk or env), removed from env dict, tracked for cleanup, swept on startup for orphans, and deleted in finally block and exit handler.\n\n4. **Cleanup Ordering**: Executor's finally block cleans up credentials, proxy, and sandbox. Main shutdown waits for `waitForCleanup()` before `process.exit()` to prevent leaks.\n\n5. **Isolation Layers**: bwrap namespace isolation (PID, UTS, network) + per-execution sandboxDir + credential file (not env) + network proxy for allow-list policies."}],"totalDurationMs":46468,"totalTokens":37657,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19665,"cache_read_input_tokens":14573,"output_tokens":3413,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19665},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
